
---


@startuml

class User {
    +name: String
    +email: String
}

class Student {
    +name: String
    +email: String
    -registered: Boolean
    -requests: List<TutoringRequest>
    -paidSessions: List<TutoringSession>
    -canceledSessions: List<TutoringSession>
}

class Tutor {
    +name: String
    +email: String
    +bankAccount: String
    -expertise: Map<String, String>  // subject -> expertise level
    -hourlyPrices: Map<String, Double>  // subject -> price per hour
    -weeklyAvailability: List<TimeSlot>
    -sessions: List<TutoringSession>
    -awards: List<String>
}

class Subject {
    +name: String
    -tutors: List<Tutor>
}

class TutoringRequest {
    +student: Student
    +tutor: Tutor
    +subject: Subject
    +level: String
    +suggestedDateAndTime: DateAndTime
    +status: String  // "pending", "confirmed", "rejected"
}

class TutoringSession {
    +id: String
    +dateAndTime: DateAndTime
    +subject: Subject
    +level: String
    +tutor: Tutor
    +student: Student
    +price: Double
    +paymentMethod: String  // "credit card", "wire transfer"
    +status: String  // "scheduled", "completed", "canceled"
    +followUpRequests: List<TutoringRequest>
}

class TimeSlot {
    +day: String
    +startTime: String
    +endTime: String
}

class DateAndTime {
    +date: Date
    +time: String
}

' Relationships
User <|-- Student
User <|-- Tutor
Student --> TutoringRequest
Tutor --> TutoringRequest
TutoringRequest --> Subject
TutoringRequest --> TutoringSession
Tutor --> Subject
Tutor --> TutoringSession
Student --> TutoringSession
Tutor --> TimeSlot
TutoringSession --> FollowUpRequest
TutoringSession --> PaymentMethod

@enduml

---

### 📌 Notes:
- **`User`** is an abstract base class for both **`Student`** and **`Tutor`**.
- **`TutoringRequest`** represents a student's request to a tutor.
- **`TutoringSession`** represents an actual session that has been confirmed.
- **`TimeSlot`** captures weekly availability of tutors.
- **`DateAndTime`** captures specific scheduling details.
- The `Tutor` class includes maps for **expertise** and **hourly prices**, which are subject-specific.
- **`PaymentMethod`** is modeled as an association (could be represented as an enum or separate class in more complex models).

